  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Low habitual intake of low-dose dark chocolate (6 g/day) has been shown to have a beneficial
      effect on arterial blood pressure in one previous study. The trial will assess if ingestion
      of a higher but still moderate dose (25 g/day) over 3 months will have a more pronounced
      effect. The population will consist of cardiovascular high-risk patients only (who will
      potentially benefit most from blood-pressure lowering).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
